<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Joe Root gave the England T20 selectors a nudge as he starred in Yorkshire’s Vitality Blast win over Derbyshire. </p>

<p>The Test captain scored 64 off 40 balls — including two sixes and seven fours — then took two wickets with his spin. </p>

<p>He is trying to make a case for inclusion in the T20 World Cup and must be putting Moeen Ali under pressure. </p>

<p>This was his fifth career T20 50 as Yorkshire reached 220-5. Adam Lyth also smashing 61 from 32 deliveries, before the Falcons stumbled to 121-9 with Root taking a career-best 2-7. </p>

<p>Test captain Joe Root (above) gave the England T20 selectors a nudge on Sunday</p>
